text: I have been using these for a while now to help me fall asleep and to stay asleep. A serving size is 2 chews.  These do come in a gummy form. I would also suggest not taking until you are ready to lay down.  I am usually so sleepy I can't stay awake within 20 minutes of taking this.  I would recommend this to anyone who has trouble falling asleep.  Also, be sure to read the ingredients and instructions because it can interact with other medications. text: I don't typically give my kids melatonin as they more often than not, go to sleep without any issues. We're not strict about bedtimes on weekends or during school vacations because they're fairly scheduled. I ended up picking this up because the kids were way off schedule during Christmas vacation and definitely needed assistance getting back on track for school. My son's bed time is at 8:30, but I decided to give him his dose at 7:50 instead of the suggested 20 minutes before bedtime. I am so glad I did. The 3mg did NOTHING for him. He was still very wide awake at 8:40. I ended up giving him half of one of my 5mg gummies and that did the trick. He didn't particularly like the flavor, but didn't hate it either. My daughter on the other hand did not like it at all. The 3mg worked slightly better for her, which struck me as a little odd because she's 5 years older and approximately 50 pounds heavier than my son, so I figured it wouldn't have worked as well. I did end up giving her half of a 5mg gummy as well. She woke up for school without any issues. She was well rested, not groggy at all. My son on the other hand, slept in much later than usual, but said he felt as though he got a good night's rest. I'll have to give these another try at some point to see if they work any better the next time around.

text: I use these for myself because they are one of the only 1mg of melatonin I can find. People need to dive into melatonin dosage research more. I'm an adult and overweight if you want to consider weight factor into dosage and when I do take this, I take half a tablet (0.5mg). I never wake up groggy after taking half a tablet and it gives me enough push to fall asleep. On 3mg  I tend to have nightmares and wake up groggy. I imagine it's the same for many adults and children but it's not widely known that melatonin should be taken in extremely small dosages because many tablets are 5mg-10mg. You and your child should be taking the smallest dose possible to help you fall asleep, not make you fall asleep. As far as this brand, I love it. I like the ingredients and although I think their dosage recommendations are too high, they're a lot better than the 10mg gummies people eat like snacks.
